:::summary
Fire is one of the most ancient and consequential phenomena in human history — a rapid chemical reaction between a fuel and oxygen that releases heat and light. The mastery of fire is what first separated humanity from every other creature on Earth, enabling warmth, cooked food, metalworking, and civilization itself. In the Bible, fire appears as a symbol of God's presence, His holiness, His purifying judgment, and His guiding care — from the burning bush to the tongues of fire at Pentecost.
